12/04/2004
LJUBLJANA, Slovenia -- Foreign Minister Dimitrij Rupel and his Croatian counterpart, Miomir Zuzul, held a joint press conference on Friday (9 April) at which they agreed relations between the two countries are developing well. 
They also expressed the willingness to continue dialogue to resolve several outstanding bilateral issues, including the Ljubljanska Bank, Piran Bay, the Krsko nuclear power plant, and Croatia's ecological and fishery zone in the Adriatic. 
(Vecernji List - 10/04/04; HINA, HIC - 09/04/04)
